Class VectorList

  • java.lang.Object
    • VectorList

  • public class VectorList
extends java.lang.Object
    The VectorList class is, as the name would imply, a data structure based around a list of Vectors. It could more accurately be described as a VectorMap, as it is based on a HashMap with the Vector name as key and Vector double array as its value. However, it is not strictly used as a HashMap, as its variable implementation as a TreeMap would suggest.
    Since:
    26-04-2019
    Author:
    Luke Byrne, Lilian Morgan, Heather Lloyd
